The paper discusses the development of a meta semantic search engine that utilizes ontology and intelligent agents to fetch results from different semantic search engines. This falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) as it deals with improving the effectiveness and efficiency of web search. Additionally, the use of ontology and intelligent agents suggests a focus on Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Database (cs.DB) technologies. The paper also mentions the analysis of snippets, which is a common technique in Natural Language Processing (cs.CL). Finally, the proposed support for image and news search suggests a potential focus on Cybersecurity (cs.CY) as these types of searches may involve sensitive or private information.
